  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "But thou shalt say unto them,.... Having found by experience, after long speaking and calling to them, that they are a disobedient and incorrigible people: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "this is a nation that obeyeth not the voice of the Lord their God; who, though the Lord is their God, and has chosen and avouched them to be his special people, whom he has distinguished by special favours; yet what he says by his prophets they pay no regard unto, and are no better than the Gentiles, which know not God: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor receiveth correction; or \"instruction\" (y); so as to be reclaimed, and made the better; neither by the word, nor by the rod; neither had any effect upon them: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "truth is perished, and is cut off from their mouth; neither faith nor faithfulness is in them; nothing but lying, hypocrisy, and insincerity. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(y)   \"neque acceperunt disciplinam\", Schmidt. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(y)   \"neque acceperunt disciplinam\", Schmidt. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
